      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIREBALL NIGHT (2) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 7th at Gosford following on from a third place finish (22.21) there the start prior. Has never missed the frame here at the trip from three starts. Has claims if he runs up to expectations. KENZIES COMET (1) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 300m at Taree Super Track two runs back then raced on speed again when finishing third at Gosford last start. Leading player again. RAINING BOURBON (8) goes very well at the course with three wins and a placing from five starts. Was out of placings last time (18.33) at Taree Super Track in a NG, finishing sixth and beaten 10 lengths. Looks well placed here and among the chances. MASERATI AVENUE (4) scored last time and appeals as a top-three prospect.",
